<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three men who were participants in the San Diego Job Corps program in Imperial 
Beach were ordered Monday to stand trial on seven robbery and four attempted 
robbery charges in incidents with illegal immigrants near the Mexican border. 
</P>
<P>
Eight undocumented workers testified during the three-day preliminary hearing 
in San Diego Municipal Court. 
</P>
<P>
Six victims each tentatively identified one or more of the three defendants, 
who are Donald Tyrone Young, 22, Ruben Augustine Saucedo, 20, and William 
Eugene Barnes, 24. 
</P>
<P>
All witnesses were videotaped in case they cannot be located at the time of the 
trial, in which case the videotapes would be shown to a jury. 
</P>
<P>
A 17-year-old co-defendant has a hearing Thursday in Juvenile Court to 
determine whether he should be tried as an adult or as a juvenile. 
</P>
<P>
Judge Howard Shore ordered the adult defendants to appear Oct. 1 in Superior 
Court for the setting of a trial date. They remain in County Jail in lieu of 
$50,000 bail. 
</P>
