<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLEWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Green Stuff: Bill Cosby has recouped his ranking as the entertainment 
world's top earner from singer Michael Jackson, Forbes magazine reports. 
</P>
<P>
Forbes issued its list of the world's highest-paid entertainers, headed by an 
estimated $115 million in earnings by Cosby in 1989 and 1990. Jackson had 
earnings of about $100 million in that period. The Rolling Stones rock group 
rose from eighth place two years ago to third place on the 1990 list, taking in 
$88 million. The cream of the Forbes "Top 40" richest entertainers were: Steven 
Spielberg, $87 million; New Kids on the Block, $78 million; Oprah Winfrey, $68 
million; Sylvester Stallone, $63 million; and Madonna, $62 million. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
