<P>
OPPOSITION GROUP'S RALLY DRAWS 30,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least 30,000 people rallied in Sofia, Bulgaria, to cheer on the opposition 
to the ruling Socialist Party. Speakers addressing the crowd emphasized the 
unwillingness of the Union of Democratic Forces to join a coalition government 
with the Socialists, the renamed Communist Party. Dimitar Ludzhev, a prominent 
opposition politician, said: "We will do everything possible (to ensure) that 
the country faces a new election in the shortest time, an election which the 
democratic forces can win . . . and the UDF and democracy will win." 
</P>
