<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TRANSIENT FOUND SHOT IN ALLEY IN VAN NUYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 45-year-old transient was in extremely critical condition Monday after he was 
found shot several times in a Van Nuys alley known as a drug trafficking area, 
Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
No arrests were made. 
</P>
<P>
The victim's name was not released pending notification of his family. 
</P>
<P>
Detective James Vojtecky said the man was found at 12:45 a.m. in an alley 
behind the 6600 block of Hayvenhurst Avenue. Patrol officers found the victim 
after several residents in the area called police and reported hearing numerous 
gunshots. 
</P>
<P>
"No motive has been established for the shooting. However, the area is known as 
a location where narcotics transactions occur," Vojtecky said. 
</P>
<P>
In April, a man was shot to death in the same alley during a drug deal, 
Vojtecky said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
