<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: RANCHO SANTIAGO COMMUNITY COLLEGE BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Here are the candidates running for the Trustee Area 2 seat on the Rancho 
Santiago Community College District Board of Trustees in the Nov. 6 election. 
</P>
<P>
Vernon S. Evans 
</P>
<P>
Age: 61 
</P>
<P>
Occupation: Vice president and county manager, Chicago Title Co. 
</P>
<P>
Background: Currently president of Rancho Santiago College Board of Trustees, 
member of the board since 1980. Former mayor of Santa Ana, former chairman of 
Santa Ana Planning Commission. 
</P>
<P>
Issues: Seeks to further development of the college's Orange campus, encourage 
joint use of public facilities and upgrade the Santa Ana campus. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Charles W. (Pete) Maddox 
</P>
<P>
Age: 42 
</P>
<P>
Occupation: Managing partner, Lido Group, a business planning firm based in 
Orange; business teacher at Rancho Santiago and Cypress colleges. 
</P>
<P>
Background: Graduate of Santa Ana College. Endorsed by the executive board of 
the Faculty Assn. of the Rancho Santiago Community College District and by the 
Classified School Employees Assn. 
</P>
<P>
Issues: Seeks to "open up the lines of communication" to the board by 
rescinding district policy requiring employees to give four days' notice in 
order to address the board at meetings. Also wants to rescind the policy 
permitting the public to address the board only before the discussion of agenda 
items. 
</P>
</TEXT>
