<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
MAN FIRES SHOTS, THEN ROBS BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Authorities are searching for a man who fired two shots into the ceiling of a 
bank before escaping with an unknown amount of cash, said Orange County 
Sheriff's Lt. Richard Olson. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured in the noon incident at the First Interstate Bank at 26281 
Avery Parkway. The man entered the bank, brandished a handgun and "fired a 
couple of rounds into the ceiling to get their attention," Olson said. He then 
took an undisclosed amount of money and escaped on foot, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
The robber was described as in his early 30s; with brown hair; 5 feet, 10 
inches tall; and wearing a light-colored baseball cap, a long-sleeved white 
shirt, faded jeans and white shoes, Olson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
