<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRL WHO WAS HIT WHILE SKATING DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
Mission Viejo 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A-9-year-old girl who was struck by a car while roller skating died Sunday of 
her injuries, a spokesman from the Orange County coroner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
The girl, Stephanie Hoelzer of Trabuco Canyon, was struck about 6:20 p.m. 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
She was taken to Mission Hospital Regional Medical Center in critical condition 
and died at 2 p.m. Sunday, a deputy coroner said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ORANGE COUNTY; ROLLER SKATING 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA091890-0085 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 277821 </DOCID>
