<P>
PRIVATE DONORS CONTRIBUTE TO GROVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAN HERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The financially troubled Grove Shakespeare Festival raised a total of $5,895 in 
private contributions over the weekend, a theater spokesperson said Monday. 
Donations of $3,200 arrived in the mail "mostly in small checks of $10 to $25." 
</P>
<P>
The rest was been raised through curtain pleas at "Othello," the current Grove 
production. 
</P>
<P>
However, the fund-raising campaign being conducted by a group of 14 Garden 
Grove civic and volunteer organizations, to raise as much as $15,000, had yet 
to produce any revenue by Monday, according to Barbara G. Hammerman, Grove's 
managing director. Hammerman claimed last week that goal would be met within a 
few days. 
</P>
<P>
The Grove is caught in a cash-flow crisis and was expected to press the City 
Council Monday evening for a continuing infusion of emergency funds.JAN HERMAN 
</P>
