</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Islamic mosque should be allowed to have exotic domes and minarets, Mayor 
Tom Bradley said Monday as he condemned as "outrageous" a recent City Council 
decision to require a proposed mosque in Granada Hills to alter its design to 
conform with the neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
Bradley made the comments in a press release while traveling in Europe. 
</P>
<P>
Mohammed Mohuiddin, president of the Islamic Center of Northridge, said he was 
encouraged by the remarks. Mohuiddin heads the congregation that last Tuesday 
won council permission to build a mosque on a 2.5-acre site near Rinaldi and 
Encino boulevards. 
</P>
<P>
