<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 ARRESTED, 2 SOUGHT IN HOSTAGE-ROBBERY 
ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies and SWAT officers arrested two suspects and were looking for 
two others following a hostage-for-ransom robbery attempt at a Bellflower home 
early Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The four would-be robbers, armed and upset about not getting paid for a used 
pickup truck they had sold, allegedly creeped into the house of the truck's new 
owner and accosted him as he took a bath, the victim's grandson said. 
</P>
<P>
They then allegedly forced the man to go to his business and get $4,000 due on 
the truck. 
</P>
<P>
The four teen-age intruders let Orlie Coca, 52, owner of a Long Beach auto 
parts store, leave alone to get the money, authorities said. Coca's wife, Lupe, 
46, and grandson, Steben, 8, were kept at their house to ensure the merchant's 
cooperation. Coca called 911 from a cellular phone, authorities said. Two 
suspects fled after waiting for Coca at a restaurant, and two others, who were 
not identified because of their age, were arrested near the home. 
</P>
