<TEXT>
<P>
Fraud Trial of 10 Soybean Traders Begins: Greed motivated 10 Chicago Board of 
Trade soybean traders to cheat their customers, a federal prosecutor said at 
the third fraud and racketeering trial stemming from an FBI probe. The trial 
follows the indictment of a clerk and 18 soybean traders after a 1988 FBI 
investigation that also covered the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. The clerk and 
eight other traders have pleaded guilty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
