<P>
PARKER AUTOMOTIVE NAMES NEW PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN O'DELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael E. Parker will step down as president and chief operating officer of 
Parker Automotive Corp. in Costa Mesa. Orange County developer and banker 
Timothy L. Strader will take over daily operations of the company, a maker of a 
proprietary chemical cleaning system for internal combustion engine fuel 
systems. 
</P>
<P>
Parker, the company's founder and major shareholder, will remain chairman and 
chief executive. Strader, a former Koll Co. vice president, is president and 
co-founder of Legacy Cos., an Irvine builder of upscale homes and commercial 
properties, and is founding chairman of CommerceBank, a 13-year-old Newport 
Beach bank with about $230 million in assets. 
</P>
<P>
Parker was recently sued for fraud by Columbia Savings &amp; Loan. His dealings 
involving bankrupt Parker North American Corp. have prompted the scrutiny of 
federal authorities. Company officials said Strader's appointment had nothing 
to do with Parker's legal woes. JOHN O'DELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
