<P>
BRITISH AEROSPACE SELLS MORE QUIET JETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
British Aerospace PLC announced it has firm orders for 25 of its BAe 146 
aircraft, with options for eight more, in a deal worth about $900 million for 
the British company. 
</P>
<P>
British Aerospace has now sold 293 of the four-engine airliner that entered 
service in 1983 and is known as the quiet jet. It can seat between 70 and 120 
passengers. 
</P>
<P>
The total value of the latest package of orders, including options on the 
additional eight aircraft and spares, approaches 500 million pounds, or $900 
million. 
</P>
