<P>
BUY THE FIRM EASILY WINS BELMONT RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Buy The Firm, ridden by Jerry Bailey, pressed the pace into the stretch and 
pulled away for a two-length victory over Steady State in the $47,000 The Very 
One Handicap at Belmont Park Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Steady State beat Sunny Roberta by 6 1/2 lengths in the 1 1/4-mile race for 
fillies and mares 3 years old and older. 
</P>
<P>
Simply Glorious was last in the four-horse field. 
</P>
<P>
The victory was the fifth in 17 starts this year for Buy The Firm, who was 
timed in 2:04 and earned $28,200. 
</P>
<P>
Buy The Firm returned $3.80 and $2.80. Steady State paid $3.20. There was no 
show betting. 
</P>
<P>
Awesome Son made a three-wide move at the top of the stretch to get into 
contention and caught Hurricane Jackson in the final strides to post a 
neck-length victory in the featured $7,200 race at Freehold (N.J.) Raceway. 
</P>
<P>
Driven by Joe Pavia Jr., Awesome Son paced the mile in 2:00 2/5 in winning his 
third consecutive race and 12th this year. It marked the fourth time in five 
starts that the gelding has won a photo finish at this meet. 
</P>
<P>
Awesome Son paid $6, $3.80 and $2.80. Hurricane Jackson paid $4.60 and $3 and 
Jou Jous Time returned $3. 
</P>
