<TEXT>
<P>
A man convicted in California of raping a 15-year-old girl and hacking off her 
arms walked out of a county jail today after serving 48 days on a petty theft 
charge. 
</P>
<P>
Lawrence Singleton, 62, initially pleaded innocent to the second-degree 
misdemeanor charge of petty theft but changed his plea July 31, citing his past 
record and saying he did not believe he could get a fair trial. 
</P>
<P>
He was released about 6 a.m. today, 12 days short of his maximum 60-day 
sentence. 
</P>
<P>
Singleton was arrested by sheriff's deputies April 8 at a Brandon drugstore in 
rural Hillsborough County after a guard spotted him taking an instant camera 
from a display. 
</P>
<P>
In California, he served eight years and four months of a 14-year sentence for 
raping the teen-ager and leaving her for dead along a roadside in central 
California in 1978. 
