<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOKYO STOCKS PLUNGE 3.82% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices plummeted on the Tokyo Stock Exchange today, with the key Nikkei 
Stock Average falling 3.82%. 
</P>
<P>
The 225-issue Nikkei lost 932.53 points to move to 23,433.04 by the close of 
morning trading. The index fell 531.865 points, or 2.13%, on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Stock traders said high oil prices, rising interest rates and pessimism over 
the situation in the Middle East discouraged investors. 
</P>
<P>
Falling prices on the bond market also pushed the market down, they said. 
</P>
