</P>
<P>
SAVING GRACE BIDS FOR 3RD WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Suzanne Broughten's Saving Grace takes a drop in class Wednesday night at Los 
Alamitos as she goes in quest of her third victory of the year in the $5,000 
conditioned trot feature. 
</P>
<P>
Seventeen were entered for the feature, necessitating a split into two 
divisions, which will go as the sixth and eighth races on the 10-race program. 
</P>
<P>
The first section is wide open, with recent winner Kami being given a slight 
edge over Dear Miss and Devil's Gate. The second division finds Saving Grace 
dropping in class and into a good spot to get her third win of the year. Her 
main adversaries will be Moscato Beach and Kimmie's April. 
</P>
<P>
In post position order, the field for the $5,000 Wednesday night main 
attraction is as follows: Moscato Beach, Nicol Tremblay in the race bike; 
Supernal, Jim Grundy; Lotto Joe, Jack Parker Jr.; Kimmie's April, Ross Croghan; 
Oso Speedy, Paul Keays; Le Mans Catch, Steve Hyman; Saving Grace, George Cliff; 
and Lady Charlee, Rick Plano. 
</P>
<P>
First post time Wednesday night will be the usual 7:30 p.m. with the admission 
gates opening at 6 p.m. 
</P>
